---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="LOD - Projects">
  <main>
    <header>
      <h1>Projects</h1>
      <p>A list of things I've worked on or am actively involved with</p>
      <hr />
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>Products</h2>

      <article>
        <header>
          <h3>Hendley</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          Hendley is a waste management application for the nuclear sector. As
          of Dec 2025 it's in a proof of concept phase.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <header>
          <h3><a href="https://seshin.squaddy.app">Seshin</a></h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          This is a successor product to Squaddy. A simple, powerful workout
          tracker built using SwiftUI. Free for all users and what I use to
          track all my workouts.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <header>
          <h3>RationBuddy</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          RationBuddy is a mobile app that helps farmers calculate their rations
          for cattle. I launched this in Jan 2025.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <header>
          <h3>The Workout Projektt</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          This was my first product and I started work on it during lockdown
          2020. The premise was simple: build a platform that let
          athletes/coaches/influencers sell workout programs to their followers.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'll write several posts about the journey over the coming weeks but
          the TLDR is that I learn huge amounts but made lots of blunders. We
          released a V1, signed up a bunch of coaches and made sales but I
          decided to pivot for a few reasons, the main one being app store fee
          split complications.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <header>
          <h3>Squaddy (V1)</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          This was our pivot from Projektt. Squaddy V1 was a mobile app that
          allowed you to create 'squads' that you invited people to and posted
          workouts in. I figured that it would grow organically from people
          creating squads and inviting their friends. This happened and we grew
          to 10k users in about 6 months. We did a major V2 rebuild to allow
          people to record and share their own diaries ~ a la Strava.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <header>
          <h3><a href="https://squaddy.app">Squaddy (V2)</a></h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          This is live on the app stores. We're slowly improving it but are no
          longer doing this full time. I had to get a day job to pay the bills
          after my wife and I had our daughter. I use Squaddy every day and love
          it. It continues to steadily grow and make us okay revenue. We'll see
          where it goes now we've given it some room to breathe!
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Websites</h2>
      <p>
        Building websites mixes the technical and creative in a way I find
        relaxing. Most of these are built with Astro, Tailwind and Alpine but
        there are some Next.js ones in the mix too. I host them all on Vercel or
        Netlify and do my design in Figma.
      </p>

      <article>
        <header>
          <h3>
            <a href="https://cloudsecure.ltd">CloudSecure landing page</a>
          </h3>
        </header>
      </article>

      <article>
        <header>
          <h3><a href="https://squaddy.app">Squaddy landing page</a></h3>
        </header>
      </article>

      <article>
        <header>
          <h3>
            <a href="https://goldenera.squaddy.app"
              >'Golden Era' workout finder</a
            >
          </h3>
        </header>
      </article>

      <article>
        <header>
          <h3><a href="https://squaddy.app/schools">Squaddy for schools</a></h3>
        </header>
      </article>

      <article>
        <header>
          <h3>
            <a href="https://amazing-rabanadas-7b0b3f.netlify.app"
              >Swim club redesign</a
            >
          </h3>
        </header>
      </article>

      <article>
        <header>
          <h3>
            <a href="https://wondrous-dolphin-b2df9b.netlify.app"
